§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $f: 𝗥^d → 𝗥$ is a probability density. ⦉

  ‖ For $i, j = 1, …, d$ and $i ≠ j$, let $f_{i | j}: 𝗥^2
    → 𝗥$ satisfy
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f_{ij}(ξ, γ) = f_{i | j}(ξ, γ)f_j(γ) ⦉
    ⦉
    for $ξ, γ ∈ 𝗥$. ⦉

  ‖ We call $f_{i | j }$ a ❬conditional density❭ of $f$. ⦉
⦉


